<h3 id="intro">Intro</h3>

<p>Client-side JavaScript has a lot of ways it can go horribly, horribly wrong. For starters, Browsers execute JavaScript with different engines, and not all interpretations are exactly the same.</p>

<p>Luckily, browsers give us some excellent tools for debugging client-side JavaScript.</p>

